Dialogue: 10,0:01:39.30,0:01:43.89,Narrator,,0,0,20,,Yumeiro Patissiere: every Monday at 6:30pm.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:43.89,0:01:45.57,Narrator,,0,0,20,,Stay tuned!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:49.13,0:01:52.15,Top,,0,0,0,,That silly Pat caused another big fuss.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:52.15,0:01:55.62,Top,,0,0,0,,Yeah... But I share the blame for that with Janet.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:55.62,0:01:57.22,Top,,0,0,0,,You two are made for each other. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.22,0:02:00.45,Top,,0,0,0,,Good-natured humour is one thing, \Nbut hurtful pranks are quite another. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:00.45,0:02:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:01.57,0:02:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel really bad for what I did to Miss Kennedy.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:04.56,0:02:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know she was such a devoted teacher.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:07.79,0:02:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But thanks to that incident, we came together \Nas a class with Miss Kennedy! {/started getting along}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:13.50,0:02:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:15.97,0:02:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's at the cost of Miss Roberts \Ngetting even more impatient with us. {lit: ended up getting more and more strict - meaning she'll be stricter in the future}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:31.64,0:02:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You forgot your textbook?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:33.77,0:02:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, although I'd prepared yesterday, \Nit just slipped my mind...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:37.06,0:02:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want any excuses!\NYou forgot your textbook, and that's that. {lit: it doesn't change the fact you forgot}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:40.33,0:02:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:41.18,0:02:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Not bringing your textbook means you have no intention of taking the class.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:45.60,0:02:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't mean to... {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.60,0:02:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But that’s how it comes across—\Nlike it or lump it! {????? lit: but even if you take it like that, there's no helping it}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:48.62,0:02:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time something like this happens \NI won't let you in. {lit: won't let you take the class}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:52.11,0:02:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and fetch it now.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:53.78,0:02:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:02.92,0:03:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasting our precious time on such nonsense...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:05.99,0:03:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Please pay attention, everyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:07.37,0:03:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.31,0:03:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Miss Roberts is so unfeeling.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:16.76,0:03:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The way she scolded me... \NShe thinks I'm a kindergartener or what?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:19.63,0:03:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,She hasn’t tolerated any nonsense in class \Nsince the fire-cracks incident. {lit: since firecrackers incident, during the class, she didn't make any kori - no clue what this kori could be, but from context probably something like "she didn't allow for any disobedience/gave no leeway"}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.74,0:03:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't really hate her, \NI respect her too much for what she's done. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.84,0:03:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither do I, but if she was a bit more charitable, \NI'd enjoy learning math a great deal more. {/tolerant}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:31.21,0:03:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't lose your heart like that, Isabel. {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:33.15,0:03:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a lacrosse match in the afternoon, \Nlet's give it our all as usual. {?? what's that sabarashi}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:36.68,0:03:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right, we won't lose today!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.82,0:03:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally! {lit: neither will I [lose]}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.56,0:04:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it, Isabel! Hooray! {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:25.30,0:04:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You're getting the hang of it, Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:27.43,0:04:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you learn the tricks, \Nthe rest comes to you naturally. {lit: the rest is technique}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:29.92,0:04:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you’ve got it. But stay on your guard—\Nwe shan’t lose next time!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.87,0:04:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but the rest of our team is strong too. {adding "the rest of" dunno what she means otherwise}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.81,0:04:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Even that girl Kathleen is doing her best now!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:38.43,0:04:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet! Kathleen has always \Nbeen good at lacrosse.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.40,0:04:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... Right. \NAnd that's why I'm praising her, don't I? {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.93,0:04:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Headmistress's birthday is coming up, so...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.76,0:04:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, the present money?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:58.33,0:05:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. We've decided \Nto chip in one shilling each.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.03,0:05:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Please prepare it, everyone! {lit: thanks for your coop[eration}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.04,0:05:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:04.62,0:05:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What'll it be this year? {the present}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:06.77,0:05:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,How about a photo frame? \NI know it's a bit banal, but... {/trite/hackneyed}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:11.56,0:05:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? But where's Kathleen?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.05,0:05:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe taking a walk?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.15,0:05:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? I'll find her later, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:15.50,0:05:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen is just stingy.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:17.88,0:05:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn’t even put in an offering \Nwhen we went to church the other day. {lit: donation when visiting a temple}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:20.97,0:05:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet! Don't smear others like that with rumors. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:23.34,0:05:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's true!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:27.34,0:05:31.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,Maybe she heard it? \NJanet, you idiot...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:07.33,0:06:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,One shilling?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:23.13,0:06:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So they sent me a boxful \Nof cakes and tinned food from home!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:26.56,0:06:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,How wonderful! So you'll be throwing a great birthday party, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:30.06,0:06:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'll treat everyone during tea time.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:32.86,0:06:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:33.63,0:06:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't wait! {paul impression}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:35.26,0:06:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there any chocolates too?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:36.90,0:06:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course! \NThere are cookies, biscuits, and whatnot.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:40.00,0:06:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:44.86,0:06:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, Hillary.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:46.61,0:06:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Kathleen? Where were you? \NI was looking for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:49.04,0:06:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I just left a little early. {lit: I went ahead and went early/first - dunno what she means if she just was on the field while everyone was in the dorm and wasn't supposed to go somewhere next}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:52.31,0:06:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, for the Headmistress's gift.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:54.58,0:06:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah, right. Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:56.65,0:07:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to give her a photo frame? \NI hope you find a nice one.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.76,0:07:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, we were just talking about how we'll celebrate my birthday this Thursday.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.23,0:07:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be treating everyone, \Nso look forward to it.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:13.67,0:07:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, really? \NThank you, Janet.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:18.87,0:07:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We gotta buy a present for Janet too!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:21.14,0:07:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna go pick one tomorrow? {lit: will we go immediately tomorrow}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:22.78,0:07:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds good. \NLet's do that!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:26.36,0:07:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Good timing! \NMy granddad just sent me ten shillings.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:30.02,0:07:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll buy a present for Janet, \Nand then also get my lacrosse stick mended. {??? dunno what's "lacrosse's cloth/kurosu"}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:34.35,0:07:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Pat. I'm worried about Kathleen.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:36.49,0:07:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:37.16,0:07:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,She seems downcast, somewhat.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:38.83,0:07:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't she always like that?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.63,0:07:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s just upset by Janet’s remarks. {/sarcasm}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:42.60,0:07:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.43,0:07:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish she was more confident \Nand knew how to held her head high.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:46.30,0:07:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But as long as she keeps slumping, \NJanet will keep teasing her.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:49.34,0:07:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When we're alone, she's always in good spirits... \NI wonder what's causing this. {lit: when just two talking - meaning when they talk privately}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.43,0:08:03.75,Thought,,0,0,0,,Good timing! \NMy granddad just sent me ten shillings.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:06.15,0:08:07.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,This isn't right.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:19.38,0:08:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?! {/What should I do?!}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.35,0:08:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They really are gone! \NMy ten shillings!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:24.61,0:08:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure I've put it in the top drawer...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.51,0:08:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The same your granddad sent you?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.24,0:08:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure you didn't leave it elsewhere?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.65,0:08:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I've searched everywhere. \NTo think I'd lose ten shillings like that...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:37.42,0:08:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We can each lend you a shilling or two.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.24,0:08:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to leave soon, we'll be late!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:41.12,0:08:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right. \NThere's no time, so I'll have to ask you. {to lend me money}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:12.22,0:09:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, maybe this?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:15.17,0:09:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's lovely! {kawai?}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:19.54,0:09:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, right? \NSo pretty!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:39.51,0:09:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Here! She's here!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:44.90,0:09:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, it's finally here! \NThe feast you've been looking forward to!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.96,0:09:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.16,0:09:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did everyone go?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.04,0:10:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy Birthday, Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:02.97,0:10:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy Birthday, Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:05.38,0:10:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations! {/happy birthday!}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:07.44,0:10:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:08.91,0:10:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But it seems to me you’re happier \Nto see what’s in this basket than to see me.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:12.71,0:10:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that certainly is a factor.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:14.51,0:10:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:15.52,0:10:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Our simple gifts.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:16.70,0:10:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! This one's from me.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.22,0:10:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you like it.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.38,0:10:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:21.06,0:10:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, everyone!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:22.42,0:10:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations, Janet.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:26.23,0:10:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This is from me.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:29.48,0:10:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Kathleen.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.20,0:10:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, come on, let's open it already! {basket, I assume}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:33.63,0:10:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:42.51,0:10:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Next is from Kathleen. \NWhat could it be?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.15,0:10:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen... I can't accept this. \NIt's too luxurious!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:56.02,0:10:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're the only one who can use it. \NTurn it around. {lit: look behind}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.30,0:11:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's amazing... Thank you!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.54,0:11:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get to opening this, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:11.80,0:11:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! Take a look at this abundance!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:14.51,0:11:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Cakes with butter, biscuits, \Nand condensed milk!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:17.34,0:11:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Some sardines too! {???????? no clue, but in book they mention that so w/e}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:18.28,0:11:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And peppermint creams!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.38,0:11:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All the things I love! \NThe next tea time will be fun!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:22.12,0:11:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's have a midnight feast! {from the book, even thou we hear party}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:24.52,0:11:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Midnight feast?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:26.69,0:11:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We used to do it at our previous school.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:28.49,0:11:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's thrilling, and {for some reason, }all food tastes better \Nin the middle of the night.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:31.56,0:11:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds fun. \NI heard some third formers did it before.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:34.62,0:11:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:35.56,0:11:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How about we all bring \Na bit of everything to the table? {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:37.86,0:11:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds good! That'd almost make it \Na proper feast. But when?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:41.13,0:11:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow's good time.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.34,0:11:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I overheard Miss Roberts talking about it.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:46.41,0:11:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s off to a concert tomorrow evening,\N and she’ll be staying at a friend’s house.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:50.32,0:11:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yahoo!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.14,0:11:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfect timing! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:52.28,0:11:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's go and tell Sheila's room too. \NWe'll get the whole class together! {sheila-tachi - i assume sheila is their classmate but they're living in two dorm rooms, hilary is overlooking this one and sheila the other one}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.35,0:11:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in! The more—the merrier!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:59.05,0:12:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Not so loud.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:02.00,0:12:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's start preparing at once! {sassoku junbi?}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:04.19,0:12:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure the others don't catch on to this. {/realize/notice}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:06.80,0:12:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Operation Midnight Feast begins!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:09.30,0:12:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:21.37,0:12:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, I'm off!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.44,0:12:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on ahead. \NI’ll just fetch my purse and catch up.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:31.22,0:12:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Aren't you going to town, Kathleen? \NEveryone else left already.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:35.05,0:12:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, I was just leaving.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:37.22,0:12:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:42.88,0:12:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.06,0:12:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Weird, I thought I still had two shillings left.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:46.93,0:12:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's strange. I'm sure I still had them \Nwhen I paid the cleaning fee this morning... {for cleaning the stove in the previous episode; dunno why they called it "cleaning" here if they called it "repairs" last ep; anyway, we clearly hear "cleaning" here so I guess there's no point to replace it with anything}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.01,0:12:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.41,0:12:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no... \NIt's not nice to suspect others like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.85,0:13:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it's my mistake.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:01.21,0:13:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... But what do I do now? \NI'll just have to borrow from Pat.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.35,0:13:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, did you see the cake?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:06.00,0:13:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that was crazy!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:09.56,0:13:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, that should be all.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.24,0:13:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's quite a lot we've gathered here.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:13.06,0:13:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:14.16,0:13:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Roberts left.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.68,0:13:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Great! I was terribly worried when she \Nso nearly scolded me in maths class today. {?? dunno why it matters now}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:20.00,0:13:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true! \N"Hey, you two. What are you fidgeting about?"
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.00,0:13:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, wrap it up now.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:36.15,0:13:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The preparations are finished.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.21,0:13:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Joan! Joan, wake up!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.87,0:13:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? Is it time already? {lit: already party? (feast) - dunno how to shoehorn it into reasonable cps}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.22,0:13:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you forget already? {lit: don't [talk] half-asleep}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:55.60,0:13:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re changing shifts.  \NIsabel will take over from you in half an hour.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:59.71,0:14:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh... I'm so sleepy.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:04.28,0:14:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about all the tasty stuff in the cupboard. {locker}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:06.98,0:14:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll help you stay up.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.86,0:14:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, it's time! Wake up!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:42.33,0:14:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:44.42,0:14:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet, Joan, Doris, it's time!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:47.79,0:14:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, Vera, you wake up too!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:50.54,0:14:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Feast time! {party yo}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:01.60,0:15:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:03.60,0:15:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,At least try not to drop the cake!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:36.27,0:15:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This bread is heavenly! {maybe by bread she refers to the sandwich as a whole}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:38.20,0:15:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Impressive! It's the great feast, all right!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.21,0:15:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure it’s even grander and more splendid \Nthan the third form’s feast was.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.51,0:15:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ta-da! Tonight's special is here.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:50.62,0:15:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Behold!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:55.59,0:15:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks delicious!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.19,0:16:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Provided by Kathleen Gregory.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:03.10,0:16:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not much of it, \Nso first come, first served! {????????? can only confidently hear "*** ga nai kara hayai *** yo", not in the book}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:05.78,0:16:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That almond icing is gorgeous!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:08.10,0:16:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Those sugar roses are something. {??????? only hear bara}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:09.62,0:16:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? There wasn't enough for Kathleen?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:11.54,0:16:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:12.21,0:16:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, I'm good. \NIt's my own fault for not bringing a bigger one.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:15.51,0:16:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,By no means! \NIt already looks awfully expensive.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.18,0:16:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It must've cost you a fortune. {, Kathleen}{from book, no clue what the JP here is ??????}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:19.50,0:16:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's nothing.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:21.35,0:16:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m most awfully glad you liked it.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:23.48,0:16:28.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry for doubting you, \Nwhen you so love to bring joy to others.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.09,0:16:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:32.89,0:16:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There aren't any gentlemen here.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:35.81,0:16:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We present to you the clown dance \Nof genius girl Doris Elward. {?????? can't make out the beginning at all}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:54.85,0:16:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Doris learnt it during the holidays \Nat some special classes. It's great fun!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.29,0:17:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, she has a talent!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:28.50,0:17:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Bother! Someone’s bound to have heard that!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:30.62,0:17:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick! Clear everything up!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:41.96,0:17:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Get into your beds!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:46.97,0:17:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen! {?????}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:04.98,0:18:06.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's Miss Kennedy.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:11.06,0:18:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's hiding there?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.59,0:18:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing at this hour of the night?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:16.95,0:18:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:18.97,0:18:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy, a mouse!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:19.93,0:18:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! A mouse?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:29.88,0:18:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, was that noise I heard \Nfrom this room just now also down to a mouse?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:33.95,0:18:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I think so, Miss Kennedy.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:36.58,0:18:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:37.75,0:18:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, I don’t see that there’s anything to report to Miss Roberts.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.50,0:18:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But you might want to see that it’s tidy \Nbefore Matron does her rounds tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:47.89,0:18:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:48.99,0:18:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:56.27,0:18:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! That was scary!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.35,0:19:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,She saw those awful ginger-beer bottles all right—\Nfancy agreeing that it might have been mice! {book}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:01.87,0:19:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My goodness! Kenny’s a sport! {book; kenny = kennedy}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.94,0:19:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She's the best teacher one could have! {lit: kind and nice}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.68,0:19:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,"Kathleen, was that noise I heard \Nfrom this room just now also down to a mouse?"
Dialogue: 10,0:19:15.17,0:19:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it seems that Miss Roberts \Nwon't find out this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:18.32,0:19:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That was fun!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:19.73,0:19:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And delicious!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:21.11,0:19:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The midnight feast was a great success!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:24.20,0:19:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{Yeah!}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:37.49,0:19:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All five of you are unwell?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:39.81,0:19:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,My stomach feels queasy... {literal, just put in any symptoms of overeating}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:51.84,0:19:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I know these symptoms very well. \NYou are suffering from Midnight Feast Illness!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:56.04,0:19:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You needn’t pretend to me!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.28,0:19:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Who told you?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:58.36,0:19:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:59.36,0:20:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But I haven’t been Matron of a girls’ school \Nfor twenty-five years for nothing!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:02.70,0:20:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,One glance at your faces \Nis enough for me to know!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:06.99,0:20:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But don't you worry—I shan’t tell tales. {book}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.64,0:20:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I always say there’s no need to punish girls \Nfor having a midnight feast,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:12.81,0:20:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for the way they feel the next day—the bitter medicine \Nthey must swallow—is punishment enough!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:22.77,0:20:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I love sardines, but I don’t think \NI’ll ever be able to look a sardine in the face again. {book}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:26.93,0:20:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Same here. \NAlthough Kathleen's cake was something else.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.00,0:20:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna try it again once.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:31.23,0:20:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of Kathleen, \Ndon't you think she's altered a lot recently?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:34.23,0:20:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. She seems much more active and happy now.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:37.57,0:20:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true. The old Kathleen was always so jumpy, you couldn't help teasing her.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:41.48,0:20:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Turns out she was always a cheerful and kind girl.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:44.13,0:20:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I've come to view Kathleen differently now.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:47.58,0:20:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, there you are! \NIsabel, Belinda Towers sent for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:51.07,0:20:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,For me?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:53.55,0:20:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder why.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:55.66,0:20:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I know about your midnight feast.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:59.44,0:21:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen told me everything.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.66,0:21:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I laughed so hard my stomach hurts now!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:04.60,0:21:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:05.38,0:21:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, our next lacrosse match \Nwill be with the St. Christopher's School.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:09.44,0:21:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The full-day school in town?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:12.24,0:21:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to put two first form players on the field. One of them is Kathleen. {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:15.61,0:21:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though I used to think her\N too weak-willed to play before.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:19.41,0:21:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Isabel?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:20.71,0:21:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You absolutely must choose Kathleen!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:22.48,0:21:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She's been acting a lot more confident lately. \NI'm sure she'll do her best!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:26.72,0:21:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And the other one is you.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.10,0:21:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Me? Not Pat?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:30.92,0:21:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat is a perfect defender, but right now \NI need a player who can score goals.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:35.26,0:21:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm impressed by the sharpness of your shots.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:37.73,0:21:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much! \NI'll do my best!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:41.03,0:21:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry I'm late.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:43.10,0:21:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I bought the biscuits.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:44.70,0:21:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:45.94,0:21:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen's treating us.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:47.16,0:21:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to buy something to celebrate myself, \Nbut I couldn't find my money.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:52.11,0:21:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Those biscuits are great!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:54.62,0:21:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve found a delightful little sweet shop.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:56.78,0:21:58.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,It happened again! Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:59.02,0:22:00.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,Kathleen...
Dialogue: 10,0:22:00.64,0:22:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Isabel and Kathleen are gonna play?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:03.61,0:22:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to tell her that Pat or Janet \Nwere much better players...
Dialogue: 10,0:22:06.96,0:22:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about? \NIf you hesitate, I'll start teasing you again! {literal, lol}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:10.76,0:22:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Go there and show them all! \NI'll come to cheer for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:13.23,0:22:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Attagirl! {lit: you've done it}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:13.90,0:22:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, I'll do my best!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:15.33,0:22:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course! I won't forgive you if you lose \Nto the likes of St. Christopher’s.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:21.47,0:22:24.94,Thought,,0,0,0,,That’s right, I shouldn’t trouble myself \Nwith any extra worries just now.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:24.94,0:22:27.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,Just give it my all \Npreparing for that lacrosse match!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:49.96,0:23:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:50.98,0:23:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.05,0:23:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Pat, I need to tell you something important. It's about Kathleen!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:55.22,0:23:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you serious? \NNo, I can't believe it...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:57.28,0:23:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to believe it either.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.17,0:24:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But when you think about it, it was when everyone’s money began disappearing
Dialogue: 10,0:24:02.44,0:24:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that Kathleen became \Nso generous and extravagant.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:05.08,0:24:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I really love Kathleen \Nthe way she is recently.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:07.81,0:24:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But if that's true, we'll have to give up on her!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:10.10,0:24:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I really want to think I'm wrong... {?????}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:13.05,0:24:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 10,0:24:14.50,0:24:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,"Poor Kathleen."
Dialogue: 10,0:24:14.50,0:24:18.94,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 6\NPoor Kathleen {かわいそうなキャサリン}{in book, I think this chapter is called "A Very Muddled Girl" and that's too far from kawaisouna kasarin to use here}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:16.04,0:24:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay tuned!
